The distance from a point \((x_0,y_0,z_0)\) to the plane \(ax+by+cz=d\) is
\[
D=\frac{\bigl|a x_0+b y_0+c z_0-d\bigr|}{\sqrt{a^2+b^2+c^2}}.
\]
Here \(a=4,\;b=2,\;c=-1,\;d=3\) and \(P=(5,-1,0)\), so
\begin{align*}
D&=\frac{\bigl|4\cdot5+2\cdot(-1)+(-1)\cdot0-3\bigr|}{\sqrt{4^2+2^2+(-1)^2}}
=\frac{|20-2-3|}{\sqrt{16+4+1}}
=\frac{15}{\sqrt{21}}
=\frac{5\sqrt{21}}{7}\,.
\end{align*}
